text.section:
The Commissioner may suspend, revoke, or refuse to renew a limited lines license to sell insurance in connection with, and incidental to, the rental of a motor vehicle issued under this subtitle after notice and opportunity for a hearing under Title 2, Subtitle 2 of this article if the motor vehicle rental company or an employee of the motor vehicle rental company has:
willfully violated this article or another law of the State that relates to insurance;
operated without a limited lines license to sell insurance in connection with, and incidental to, the rental of a motor vehicle as required under this subtitle;
failed to provide required disclosures;
offered or sold unapproved insurance products;
failed to hold an appointment with the insurer;
failed to train employees selling or soliciting, or negotiating the sale of, insurance products on behalf of the motor vehicle rental company; or
misrepresented pertinent facts or policy provisions that relate to the coverage offered or sold pursuant to this subtitle.
